      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions - Improvements to consider] Line 358: The merged push-event subscription is unbounded and releases the push hold after any later message/call/request event, regardless of whether it belongs to the push currently being processed. If an unrelated daemon event occurs shortly after `onPushProcessed()` decrements the counter, the foreground service and WakeLock can be released before the pushed work has completed. Correlate the release condition to the pushed account/conversation/call where possible, or keep the full timeout unless a daemon event can be confidently tied to the push payload.",
